  "prompt": "If you block someone on Instagram could they still see you in the followers list of an account that didn't block them and they already know?",
  "response": "If you block someone on Instagram, they will no longer be able to see **your profile**, posts, stories, or any of your activity on the platform. However, if they are still following an account that you also follow (and that account hasn't blocked them), they **can still see your profile in the followers list** of that mutual account. Here\u2019s why:\n\n1. **Blocking on Instagram only restricts direct interaction between you and the blocked account**. It doesn\u2019t remove your presence entirely from the platform or from mutual accounts.\n   \n2. If the blocked person visits the followers list of an account you both follow, they will still see your username and profile picture. However, if they try to click on your profile, they won\u2019t be able to access it because you\u2019ve blocked them.\n\nIn summary, they can still see your presence in mutual followers lists, but they won\u2019t be able to view your profile or interact with you directly.",
